  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-12-17",
    "date": "2021-02-11T19:25:15Z",
    "text": "Addressing Climate Financial Risk Act of 2020 \n\nThis bill establishes the Climate Risk Advisory Committee that must consult with the Financial Stability Oversight Council of the Department of the Treasury regarding a report on the impact of climate risk on U.S. financial stability.\n\nAdditionally, the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency, the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, and the National Credit Union Administration must include climate risk in the guidance provided to a supervised financial institution."
  },
